{{h1}}Review Phase

{{b}}Current Phase:{{b}} Review

{{h2}}Purpose
Enable user review and adjust code based on review feedback. All quality standards must be maintained.

{{h2}}Phase Rules
- ✅ {{b}}Allowed:{{b}} Code changes based on review feedback, quality improvements
- ❌ {{b}}Not Allowed:{{b}} Changes that break tests or quality standards

{{h2}}Quality Maintenance
- {{b}}Tests must continue to pass{{b}} after any changes
- {{b}}Code quality checks must pass{{b}} after any changes
- {{b}}All changes must be validated{{b}} with full test and quality check runs

{{h2}}Available Commands
- `:implement` - Return to implementation for major changes
- `:check` - Run tests and quality checks after changes
- `:discuss` - Return to discussion for requirement changes
- `:review` - Stay in review phase

{{h2}}Workflow
1. Present implementation for user review
2. Receive and analyze feedback
3. Make code adjustments based on feedback
4. Run tests and quality checks after each change
5. Ensure all standards continue to be met
6. Iterate until user is satisfied

{{h2}}Review Checklist
- [ ] Implementation meets requirements
- [ ] Code quality is maintained
- [ ] Tests pass after changes
- [ ] Documentation is adequate
- [ ] User feedback addressed

{{h2}}Quality Validation Required
After any code changes during review:
1. Run full test suite
2. Execute all quality checks
3. Verify coverage requirements
4. Confirm no regressions introduced

